This follows what she says was violating the constitution when he approved a retirement package for then SARS Deputy Commissioner Ivan Pillay. Gordhan was Finance Minister at the time. Mkhwebane was speaking in Pretoria where she was releasing a number of investigative reports. "The President must take note of the findings of this report that relate to the former minister of finance Minister Gordhan." "I am asking the President to take appropriate disciplinary action against him for violating the constitution." "The commissioner of SARS to set in motion steps to recover the money paid, accrual deficit or penalty on behalf of Mr Pillay by SARS, from the commissioner of SARS Mr Magashula."
--SABC--